gomodel:SYNGO_5340  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 5: overexpression of deubiquitinating enzyme USP6 (construct described in Fig. 1c) in mouse cortex and hippocampus increased abundance levels for NMDAR subunits (GRIN1/2A/2B) and PSD95 (DLG4) but not AMPARs (GRIA1/2) nor synaptophysin.\n\nFigure 5d: overexpressed USP6 is present in synaptosomal and PSD biochemical fractions prepared from mouse cortex.\n\nFigure 6: USP6 interacts with NMDA receptors as demonstrated by coimmunoprecipitations in mouse brain lysates.\n\nFigure 7: USP6 attenuates NMDA receptor ubiquitination and enhances NMDA receptor stabilization.\n\nFigure 8: USP6 depletion reduces GluN1 expression in ESC-derived human excitatory neurons.\n\nFinally, authors summarise with a cartoon in Figure 9.. Experimental description: M&M: \"CAM-USP6 and Nestin-USP6 transgenic mice were produced by Cyagen Biosciences. Briefly, the sequence of the CamK2a promoter (1,294 bp) or the Nestin promoter and the coding sequence of USP6 (NM_004505.2) with a C-terminal HA tag were inserted into a PiggyBac vector to generate a pPB[Exp]-Promoter>hUSP6/HA construct.\"\n\nnote that this NCBI GenBank accession is the human protein sequence" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-12" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_5340" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9606" .

